UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.AllowPortSelect: Determines if the Patchwork Tool can access any cable input or output ports on the device.
Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. Pre-game includes all phases prior to start of game (like the pre-game lobby or countdown to start of game.) This setting does not affect Edit Mode.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.GridHeight.Desc: Determines the vertical height of the Note Grid so that more or fewer notes are available.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Disable.Descrip: Disables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Enable.Descript: Enables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.LegalInfo.Descr: Please note: Use of a Patchwork audio device is limited to the creation of new and original musical works.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Page.Descriptio: Select which page is shown and played on the Note Grid. Each page can contain its own pattern of notes.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Style.Descripti: Selects the style for the chosen Step Rate. "Straight" will output at the Step Rate, "Triplet" will output in a shuffle feel at two thirds of the Step Rate, and "Dotted" will output in a syncopated feel at one and a half times the Step Rate.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.NoteOut.Descrip: Sets the destination for this device's Note Out cable.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.AutoPageIn.Desc: Sets the inputs for this device's Auto Page toggle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.LengthIn.Descri: Sets the inputs for this device's Length knob.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.OctaveIn.Descri: Sets the inputs for this device's Octave knob.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.PageIn.Descript: Sets the inputs for this device's Page knob.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.RateIn.Descript: Sets the inputs for this device's Rate carousel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.StyleIn.Descrip: Sets the inputs for this device's Style carousel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Length.Descript: Sets the number of steps per page.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.SquareLength.De: Sets the speed at which the Note Sequencer moves through steps.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.Octave.Descript: Shifts the octave up or down for the entire sequence of notes.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.AutoPage.Descri: Toggles whether the sequencer cycles through every populated page, or remains on the current page only.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.OnDisabled.Desc: Triggers an event when the device is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.OnEnabled.Descr: Triggers an event when the device is enabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.AutoPagePlaysBl: When enabled, Auto Page will include blank pages when cycling through pages automatically.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.IsMonophonic.De: When set to OFF, allows multiple notes to be placed on the same step of the Note Grid. Use this when sending output to polyphonic devices like the Instrument Player that can play multiple notes at the same time. Monophonic devices like the Omega Synth can only play one note at a time.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.bLoop.Descripti: When set to OFF, the sequencer will play through its pattern once when enabled, then return to its disabled state.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricSequencer_C.IsChromatic.Des: When set to ON, allows semitones to be placed on the Note Grid. Semitones are a smaller musical interval.
